). Palp with femur twice as long as tibia. Cymbium long, with the distal two-thirds much narrower than the basal third. Bulb inserted at the proximal third of the cymbium, with a slender apex and embolus curved at tip.

Female ( IBSP 144085 ):
Coloration as in male, except carapace and chelicerae darker and abdomen with brown triangular marks dorsally (
Fig. 6
). Total length 15.8 ; carapace, 6.8 long, 4.6 wide. Chelicearae without conspicuous frontal thickened setae. Cephalic region more elevated and convex than in the male (
Fig. 7
). Labium, endites and sternum as in male (
Fig. 8
). Palpal tarsus, with femur half the tibia length and tarsus with one prolateral macrosetae and one claw without teeth. Legs as in males, differing in size and number of macrosetae (
Figs 9–10
). Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 5.8 , patella 2.5 , tibia 5.6 , metatarsus 5.1 , tarsus 1.3 , total 20.3 ; II, 5.5 , 2.5 , 5.6 , 4.9 , 1.4 , 19.9 ; III, 4.55 , 2.2 , 4.35 , 4.1 , 1.25 , 16.45 ; IV, 4.9 , 2.3 , 5.05 , 3.85 , 1.4 , 17.5 . Spination: leg I, femur d 0-1 - 0-1 - 0-1 -0, p0-0-0- 0-1 - 1 -0, v0, r0; patella d0, p0, v0, r0; tibia d0, p 1 - 0-1 / 2 - 0-1 /0-0,
